ing their customs, practices, and beliefs. Judaisms is the first book to assess and summarize Jewish history from the time of the Hebrew Bible through today using multiple perspectives. Ideal for classroom use, Judaismsprovides a synthetic and coherent alternative understanding of Jewish identity for students of all backgrounds;focuses on both the history of and potential futures for physical and ideological survival;includes an array of engaging images, many in color;offers extensive online resources including notes, key terms, a timeline of major texts, and chapter-by-chapter activities for teaching.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJudaism. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  aborders.  aculture.  afuture.  agenocide.  aintroduction to judaism.  ajewish religion.  ajudaism.  akosher.  alaw.  amessiah.  amysticism.  anarrative.  apower.  areligion and faith.  asinai.  aspirituality.  azion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028135640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096000840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520960008423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520960008/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY